cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.GR, cs.NA 

The paper discusses computational photography and compressive capture of images, videos, multi-spectral data, and light-fields. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the use of wavelets and backprojection, which are common techniques in multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper discusses the statistical properties of natural images, which is related to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
